Processes log entries from an input mongo collection (typically a capped collection) into
a normal collection (possibly with an automatic expiry on the records -- see db/build.js).

Build example:
$ mongo my_log --eval "var name='events', size=1024, ttl=86400" db/build.js

Call example:
$ bundle exec ruby bin/service.rb --conn mongodb://localhost   \
                                  --db my_log                  \
                                  --name events                \
                                  --ruby-safe-processor        \
                                  --time-processor             \
                                  --rails-controller-processor \
                                  --session-id-processor       \
                                  --labelled-hashes-processor  \
                                  --hashes-processor
